issue.title: Add Post
issue.body: The add post form should be accessible from the posts list. The add post form should collect a post title and body. The post should be scoped to the currently active location and category.

issue.title: Individual Post
issue.body:
If a user clicks on a post from the posts list, they should be shown a screen of an individual post containing the following info:

- Post title
- Post body
- Post comments

The user should be able to reply to the post, which should add a comment to the list.

issue.title: Visa + Immigration
issue.body:
After registering, users should be asked to optionally provide information about a visa (if they have one), if they're a green card holder, etc.

*Note:* This task needs to be fleshed out more once we identify what kind of information is useful to collect.

issue.title: Switching categories using the search bar doesn't reload the page
issue.body: There's some kind of re-rendering issue when the route changes. Refreshing the page after selecting the category fixes it. I've addressed this before in Maple, but I forget how.

issue.title: Posts
issue.body: Once a user selects a category, they should see a list of posts in that category. At all times, the posts a user sees will be scoped to a location and a category.

issue.title: Categories
issue.body:
Once registered, a user should land on the categories list. Categories might expand later, but for the purposes of our initial MVP, our categories are:

- Housing
- Employment
- Events

issue.title: Profile
issue.body: After registering, users should be asked to optionally provide their picture, name, and a short bio.

issue.title: Community + Location
issue.body: After registering, a user must specify their community and location. Examples of a community include Bosnian, Pakistani, etc. Examples of a location include St. Louis, San Fransisco, etc.

issue.title: Register
issue.body: Allow users to create an account on Nearby. Collect an email address and password, and create the account in Firebase.
